When I was living at my parents house, I used to have dreams about living in a separate bedroom with a huge t.v. of my own. That never happened, but as an adult, I treat my private section of our apartment the same way. I cherish it. All people, male or female need that space. When someone tries to barge into that space, it's painful, and I respond by establishing boundaries.

Regarding the question about women's rights: the thing is, when you deny full personhood to women, you are cutting off one of the only ways to hold men accountable to their own best behavior. That doesn't mean that women are angels and never abuse the role of a woman- of course they do sometimes, because they are only human. What it means though is that the denial of women's full humanity, in effect and programmatically, is the bread and butter of male violence.We cannot truly have equal rights until we have full personhood for women.

Hilarious! Some of those guys were...really overcompensating.

God help you, lesbian girls. I was blown away at the number of guys believing that all gay/lesbian guys were reproductive-behavioral predators.A turn off for sure.
